# Professional Employee Management System API Tests
# Run these requests to test the enhanced features

### 1. Login as admin to get JWT token
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/signin
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "password"
}

### 2. Get all employees (should show professional fields)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/employees
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_token}}

### 3. Get employee status enum values
GET http://localhost:8080/api/employees/enums/statuses
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_token}}

### 4. Get employment type enum values
GET http://localhost:8080/api/employees/enums/employment-types
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_token}}

### 5. Get security level enum values
GET http://localhost:8080/api/employees/enums/clearance-levels
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_token}}

### 6. Get employee statistics
GET http://localhost:8080/api/employees/government-stats
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_token}}

### 7. Get employees by status (Active)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/employees/by-status/ACTIVE
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_token}}

### 8. Get employees requiring background check renewal
GET http://localhost:8080/api/employees/background-check-renewal
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_token}}

### 9. Get employees with expiring contracts
GET http://localhost:8080/api/employees/expiring-contracts
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_token}}

### 10. Get employees in probation
GET http://localhost:8080/api/employees/in-probation
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_token}}

### 11. Change employee status (example: change employee ID 1 to SUSPENDED)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/employees/1/status
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "newStatus": "SUSPENDED",
  "reason": "Security incident investigation",
  "changedBy": 1
}

### 12. Update employee security level (example: employee ID 1)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/employees/1/clearance
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "clearanceLevel": "CONFIDENTIAL",
  "backgroundCheckStatus": "Completed",
  "backgroundCheckDate": "2025-11-05"
}

### 13. Create a new employee with professional defaults
POST http://localhost:8080/api/employees
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "john.smith",
  "email": "john.smith@blackdot.com",
